          <msContents>
            <summary>Agreement dated June 16, 1278, fixing boundaries of land, probably in Corsignano (rebuilt in the 15th century as Pienza by Pope Pius II, formerly Aeneas Silvius Piccolomini), involving members of the Piccolomini family, including Renaldus di Turchio (with the title of procurator), Bernardinus di Roma, and Cione d'Alamanno Piccolomini. Notarized by Jacobus filus Bartolomei or Giacomo di Bartolomeo.</summary>
            <textLang>In Latin</textLang>
